1044  	 	EARLIEST KNOWN (?) USAGE OF THE BERMUDA 1st GOVERNMENT ISSUE ON COVER - 1/- RATE TO G.B. WITH RARE RED HAMILTON "PAID/H" P5 C.D.S.; Fine 28 Sept. 1865 env. (flap lost) to London endorsed "Via Halifax" and franked by a 1st Issue 1/- Green (slight corner wrinkle does not detract) tied by a loverly strike of the Hamilton barred "2" Numeral in black, but also having a very fine rare red Hamilton "BERMUDA/H/PAID" c.d.s. (normally struck in black on stamped covers from at least as early as Nov. 1865) alongside, with a fine red 2 Oct. London arrival c.d.s. It appears that no earlier cover with this first official Bermuda issue has been recorded (only a handful of 1865 usages on cover are known), though official records indicates (and SG lists) the date of 
issue as 25 Sept. 1865. Important early stamped cover. PHOTO.  	£750
{{auction: Cavendish January 2009, The Geoffrey Osborn Bermuda Collection}}
</p>
