1047  	 	THE VERY RARE FANCY OVAL BLUE "FORWARDED BY/J MALLABY HIGGS,/Bermuda." F.A.C. ON COVER TO U.S.; Spectacular and attractive stampless 22 May 1868 env. (+ contents; opened out for display) from "St. Georges, Bermuda" (a family letter from a "Chief Mate" on a whaling ship) to "Acushnet(?), Mass., USA" having a superb blue crinkle-framed oval "FORWARDED BY/J. MALLABY HIGGS./Bermuda" cachet (much the finer of the two recorded examples) nicely placed on the lower flap; charged as an unpaid incoming Ship Letter on arrival at Boston with very fine "SHIP" and "6" marks on the front matching the adjacent mostly v. fine "BOSTON/MASS./*" 'cork' Duplex alongside. Very few Forwarding Agent cachet covers are known, and this was the sole example of this type recorded by Forand & Freeland (illustrated by them on p.99). Marvellous Exhibition Item. PHOTO.  	£1500
