1051  	 	IRELAND ISLAND - SCARCE "I/PAID" C.D.S. ON RARE 7d-RATE COVER TO G.B. "VIA NEW YORK"; 29 Jan. 1869 env. (minor closed tears at top clear of stamps & marks) to Kent endorsed "Via New York" and "Naval Officer's Letter" unusually franked by 1st Issue 6d Dull Purple + 1d Rose-red tied by a single partly fine Ireland Island barred "3" numeral with a matching scarce mostly v. fine black "BERMUDA/I/PAID" c.d.s. on the front. Carried by SS 'Fah-Kee' to NY (delayed by storms en route) and then by Cunard SS 'Russia' to Queenstown. This special 7d rate (1d credited to the US) was only available from 1868 to 1877 and was very little used; this is particularly unusual coming fram Ireland Island and being a Naval Officer's Letter. PHOTO.  	£300
{{auction: Cavendish January 2009, The Geoffrey Osborn Bermuda Collection}}
</p>
