1053  	 	MANGROVE BAY - EARLIEST RECORDED COVER (?) - RARE "4" NUMERAL & "BERMUDA/MB/PAID" MARKS; 13 Nov. 1869 env. to Edinburgh franked by 1st Issue 1/- Green (few short perfs) tied by a partly fine very rare Mangrove Bay "4" barred oval (there was no example on cover in the Ludington Collection) with a mostly very fine and equally rare black "BERMUDA/MB/PAID" c.d.s. (P5 type; earliest known date) alongside, with red crayon "11d" (credit to GB) and a fair red "PAID/LIVERPOOL/BR. PACKET" c.d.s. nearby. Mangrove Bay was the smallest of the four POs on the island at this time and this is believed to be the earliest recorded cover (Proud records nothing before Jan. 1871). Attractive and Important Sub-Offices Exhibition Item. PHOTO.  	£500
